<translate>
<!--T:210-->
== Trivia ==
* VRCat's name is a play on ''VRChat''.
* VRCat was inspired by the cat of VRChat's Head of Community Tupper, Trogdor<ref>Parzeval. (2024, August 15). Tupper: The Future of VRChat & The Life of VRChat's Head of Community | VF1 [Video]. YouTube. <tvar name="14">https://youtu.be/0YVHHtc5CsY?t=3519</tvar></ref>.
* VRCat's design originated from a call between VRChat's Art Director Rocktopus, then-Chief Creative Officer Ron, and Tupper, in collaboration with an outside design firm. The orange tabby appearance was chosen after Tupper looked at his own orange tabby cat.<ref name="devqa24apr2026">[<tvar name="15">https://ask.vrchat.com/t/april-24-2026-developer-stream-q-a-summary/48352</tvar> "April 24 2026 Developer Stream Q&A Summary"] on ''[[<tvar name="16">Special:MyLanguage/ask.vrchat.com</tvar>]]''. Posted {{#time: F j, Y | <tvar name="17">April 27, 2026</tvar> }}. Retrieved {{#time: F j, Y | <tvar name="18">June 18, 2026</tvar> }}.</ref>
* VRChat has described VRCat's age as "soft canon", treating it as roughly five years measured from the character's first public appearance, while noting that it is not officially fixed.<ref name="devqa24apr2026" />
* VRCat's arch-nemesis was [[<tvar name="19">Special:MyLanguage/VRRat</tvar>|VRRat]]. However since VRChat's release of the festive stickers they appear to now be friends<ref><tvar name="20">https://www.tiktok.com/@vrchat/video/7449076969305820462</tvar></ref>.<!-- cannot write for the life of me rn this needs to sound better lol -->
* VRCat's Quick Menu dialogue has numerous grammatical errors and inconsistencies with capitalization, such as VRChat Udon being referred to as both "Udon" and "UDON".
* VRCat's dialogue has several references to pop culture and internet memes:
** Why do I hear boss music?: Reference to a Terraria meme featuring a player character saying "why do I hear boss music"<ref><tvar name="21">https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/why-do-i-hear-boss-music</tvar></ref>.
** Sorry Dave, I can't do that right now: Reference to a line in 2001: A Space Odyessey.
** Perfect Gem Activated: Reference to the "Chat Gem" in Diablo II<ref><tvar name="22">https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki/Chat_Gem</tvar></ref>.
** Zug zug: Reference to World of Warcraft's Orcish language, a form of acknowledgement and agreement<ref><tvar name="23">https://warcraft.wiki.gg/wiki/Orcish_(language)</tvar></ref>.
** Reticulating Splines: Reference to several Maxis games, such as SimCity, SimCopter, The Sims up to Sims 4. Often showing up in loading screens.
** Downloading more RAM: Reference to a meme where an internet forum user asked "how to download more RAM," this is amusing as RAM is physical hardware that must be bought, and cannot be downloaded<ref><tvar name="24">https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/download-more-ram</tvar></ref>.
* [<tvar name="25">https://web.archive.org/web/20180815000000*/VRCat.club</tvar> VRCat.club] (Archive.org link) was an unofficial forum for the VRChat community that predates VRCat and the current ask.vrchat.com forums<!-- Tupper still owes me a steak dinner for that one. -owlboy -->
* VRCats back can be seen when you flip your [[<tvar name="26">Special:MyLanguage/Quick Menu</tvar>|quick menu]] around visually.

